The more I think about it, shouldn't the time dimension be added in a separate method? Like so

```
    def _encode_time(new_data, epoch):
        if 'time' in new_data.coords:
            new_data['time'].encoding['units'] = epoch
            new_data['time'].attrs['standard_name'] = 'time'
            new_data['time'].attrs.pop('bounds', None)
        return new_data

    def _add_time_dimension(data_array):
        if not _has_time_dim_or_coord(data_array):
                return data_array.expand_dims('time')
        return data_array

    def _has_time_dim_or_coord(data_array):
         return 'time' in data_array.dims or 'time' in data_array.coords
```

