@justinvholt - For clarity,  the term subcommand is in reference to commands that fall under another command. For example, running `cci task --help` or `cci task` both produce the same output, and show a list of available commands that fall under `cci task`. These commands (`doc`, `info`, `list`, `run`) are considered the sub-commands of the `cci task` command (which does nothing on its own. 

Maybe we should just use the word "command" instead of subcommand.

Options are provided to specific commands in the format of either a name/value pairs (i.e. --option-name value) or, in the case of a "flag" by just specifying the name of the flag (e.g. `--debug`).

